Wash and dry all produce. Preheat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Core and dice @Roma tomato{1}(quartered and diced).

Add @Gemelli pasta{12%ounce} to boiling water. Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain when finished.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large tall-sided pan over medium heat. Add onions and toss until softened, about ~{5%minutes}. Add tomatoes and toss until broken down, another ~{5%minutes}. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Wilt the spinach: Stir @spinach{5%ounce} into pan to wilt. (HINT: You may need to work in stages.) Season with salt and pepper. Remove pan from heat.

Add drained pasta, @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, @butter{1%tablespoon}, and @cheddar cheese{1%cup}. Thoroughly combine to melt cheeses. Slowly add @milk{1%cup} 1 Tablespoon at a time to reach a creamy consistency (we used roughly ½ cup). Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If pasta isn't hot enough to melt cheeses, place pan over low heat.

Broil and serve: Sprinkle with @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and remaining @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}. Transfer to oven and broil until melted and golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. (TIP: Keep a close eye on it!) Serve the mac and cheese divided between bowls and enjoy.